==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
Of Hebrew origin [[יהוּדה]] {{HH|3063}} or perhaps [[יטּה]] {{HH|H3194}}

===Pronunciation===
Ἰουδά / Iouda / ee-oo-dah'

===Proper noun===
'''Ἰουδά'''

# Judah (that is, Jehudah or Juttah), a part of (or place in) Palestine: - [[Judah]].

